The President, Graduate School, International University of Japan, Niigata, Japan, Professor Hiroyuki Itami, said Africans must learn the dynamics of Japan development methods and try to implement them in their countries. He made the remark on Monday when select African journalists visited that university to find out how the Business Education Initiative for Youth (ABE-Initiative) programme was fairing. ABE-Initiative is carried out by Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA), to support young personnel who can be move to the development of industries in Africa. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE According to him, it is the job of those passed through the programme to transfer the knowledge to gain independence and try to implement it. My impression about Nigeria changed when I arrived – Envoy Africa’s eyes on Asia ALI Media Fellowship: A flight to a new life experience Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin